text: David Kemp Karnes (December 12, 1948 â€“ October 25, 2020) was an American Republican politician, businessman, and attorney. He was a United States Senator from Nebraska from 1987 to 1989. He was president and chief executive officer of The Fairmont Group Incorporated. Karnes was born in Omaha, Nebraska. In 2019, Karnes was diagnosed with squamous-cell carcinoma, a type of skin cancer. He died on October 25, 2020 from the disease in Boston, Massachusetts at the age of 71. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1948 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from squamous-cell carcinoma Category:United States senators from Nebraska Category:Lawyers from Omaha, Nebraska Category:Businesspeople from Omaha, Nebraska Category:Politicians from Omaha, Nebraska Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
